5:
Oh, it looks like there's a flea market
going on.
8:
Hehe, these kinds of events tend to
have items you can't find in normal
stores.
13:
Excuse me, are all these books for
sale?
15:
They sure are. Those are magic
textbooks, they're needed for some
course over at Voluntas, apparently.
They're used, but feel free to take a
look!
18:
Hmm... These are very easy to
understand. What splendid
textbooks.
27:
Perhaps a little. As a knight, I
received a basic education myself.
29:
That being said, resources were
scarce, and the books we procured
were often rather impenetrable... It
was no easy task.
38: Hey, Cecilia, could I ask you a favor?
40: I want you to be my teacher.
44: Stella, can we borrow this table?
47: Sure... Did you buy some books?
54: You didn't need to tag along, Phiria.
59:
W-well, I... I thought this would be a
good opportunity to review what I've
learned...
63:
Cecilia has taught me before, but I
haven't been studying lately...
67:
That makes sense, I guess... Ahem,
Cecilia, you can start whenever
you're ready.
71:
Alright... To be perfectly honest,
though, I am not sure where we
should begin our academic
pursuits...
74:
I suppose we could begin by
determining what level of
knowledge you both possess. How
about a simple test?
75:
Lady Phiria, this will be a review for
you. We shall see how much you
remember.
86:
Hmm. I'm not quite sure how to
articulate this...
89:
Phiria... You may look smart, but
you're actually as dumb as I am.
100:
D-don't fret, Lady Phiria. Academic
studies must occur on a regular
basis, lest the lessons we learn be
forgotten.
103:
I believe it is best we take a slow
and steady approach to our lessons,
then.
107:
Good idea... Phew... It'll be tough, but
I'll do whatever I can to learn.
111:
An admirable attitude to have. I
shall provide whatever assistance I
can.
114:
Why the sudden interest though?
This appears to be an impulsive
decision, but you're quite committed
to it.
120:
Do you remember what we talked
about at the anniversary festivities?
122:
I knew nothing, yet I never tried to
learn either.
124:
Before I came to Starview, I had no
idea what humans were like.
128:
I was... the same way... I didn't even
know what I was fighting...
131:
I could make all sorts of excuses, like
that I was raised in the boonies, or
that I was a mere underling in the
army, but...
134:
Since coming here, I've come to
know humans... I've even become,
uh, f-friends with you two.
135:
Now... I'm scared of my past
ignorance. All I did was fight without
knowing what I was fighting for.
138:
I don't ever want to go into a battle
clueless again.
141:
That's why I must learn more. About
humans, fiends... and you two.
145:
Jeez, look at me being all serious! I
may talk big, but I still don't know
HOW to study, so that's why I asked
for your help.
151:
You can count on me, Arly. As your
friend, I will teach you everything I
know.
155:
A-and Arly, please tell me more
about fiends... and yourself as well!
158:
Of course. We've all got a lot of work
ahead of us.
164:
Ah, so this is where you all are. I
made snacks, so if anyone wants
some, come to the dining hall.
166:
If you see anybody else along the
way, pass on the message, okay?
170:
U-um... I would say taking a break is
just as important as studying...
Wouldn't you?
174:
Took the words right out of my
mouth.
178:
Well, this is an appropriate place to
stop, so shall we make our way over?
187:
It's nothing. It's just... Arly has
changed a lot. Even I can trust her
now.
192:
Hey, aren't you guys hungry? If you
don't hurry, the snacks will be all
gone.
195: Right. We'll be over in a moment.
